@page "/"

<MudContainer Class="mx-6 px-n4">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" Class="my-4 px-n4">Home</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Align="Align.Justify">
        <p>
            In this webapp, <b>survey instruments</b> are handled and stored. The application provides access to
            the survey instrument catalog together with usage statistics for the available configurations.
        </p>
        <p>
            Survey instruments can be defined using either the <b>Wolff and de Wardt</b> wellbore position
            uncertainty model or the <b>ISCWSA</b> wellbore position uncertainty models. For the ISCWSA family,
            two survey-tool sub-choices are supported: <b>magnetic</b> and <b>gyro</b>.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Wolff and de Wardt model represents the classical systematic-error approach for borehole position
            uncertainty. The ISCWSA magnetic and gyro models extend this area with standardized error-model
            formulations for modern directional survey tools, with separate treatment for magnetic MWD tools and
            gyroscopic survey tools.
        </p>
        <p>
            The survey instrument catalog is populated with a selection of commonly used survey instruments, with
            their associated error models and configurations. Usage statistics are collected to provide insights
            into the most commonly used survey instruments and configurations in the industry.
        </p>
        <p>
            Main references:
        </p>
        <p>
            Wolff, C.J.M. and de Wardt, J.P. 1981. "Borehole Position Uncertainty - Analysis of Measuring Methods
            and Derivation of Systematic Error Model." <i>J. Pet. Technol.</i> 33 (12): 2338-2350.
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.2118/9223-PA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://doi.org/10.2118/9223-PA</a>
        </p>
        <p>
            Williamson, H.S. 2000. "Accuracy Prediction for Directional Measurement While Drilling."
            <i>SPE Drill. &amp; Completion</i> 15 (4): 221-233.
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.2118/67616-PA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://doi.org/10.2118/67616-PA</a>
        </p>
        <p>
            Torkildsen, T., Havardstein, S.T., Weston, J.L., and Ekseth, R. 2008. "Prediction of Wellbore Position
            Accuracy When Surveyed With Gyroscopic Tools." <i>SPE Drill. &amp; Completion</i> 23 (1): 5-12.
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.2118/90408-PA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://doi.org/10.2118/90408-PA</a>
        </p>
    </MudText>
</MudContainer>
